12/06/2003
ANKARA, Turkey -- Economy Minister Ali Babacan said Wednesday (11 June) that the ruling Justice and Development Party is considering changing some parliamentary procedures to accelerate adoption of legislation required by the IMF.
The legislation includes an amendment to the social security law and a change in the execution and bankruptcy act.
The change in parliamentary procedure would facilitate their quick adoption, Babacan said.
(Hurriyet - 12/06/03;
Anadolu Agency - 11/06/03)
